CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 2, 1946, pg. 13, reads: "Island Party - Alpha Kappa Alpha sorors entertained a group of university students Thursday evening at a 'rushing' party, held at the home of Miss Shirley Butler of Avalon Street.  It is easy to see from the costumes that these lassies fell right in tune with the atmosphere of the occasion. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Kappa Alpha sorority members and candidates wearing leis, including Marilyn Ware on right in second row, posed in room with cloud patterned background and floor covered in confetti or sawdust, in home of Shirley Butler
